Plain-Language Summary (Human-Readable Summary)

This license allows others to freely share — that is, to copy and redistribute — the Licensed Material in any medium or format, provided that they comply with three core conditions: (1) Attribution must be given to the original creator; (2) the material may only be used for NonCommercial purposes — it may not be sold, monetized, or used for commercial gain; and (3) No Derivatives are permitted — the material may not be remixed, transformed, adapted, translated, or otherwise modified. No additional restrictions may be placed on recipients. This summary is provided for convenience only and has no legal effect. The full legal code governs.

Section 1 — Definitions
For the purposes of this License, the following terms shall have the meanings set forth below:

“Licensed Material” means the artistic or literary work, database, or other material to which the Licensor applied this Public License.

“Licensor” means the individual(s) or entity(ies) granting rights under this Public License, identified as [LICENSOR NAME / YOUR NAME].

“You” (or “Your”) means the individual or entity exercising the Licensed Rights under this Public License. “Your” has a corresponding meaning.

“Share” means to provide material to the public by any means or process that requires permission under the Licensed Rights, such as reproduction, public display, public performance, distribution, dissemination, communication, or importation, and to make material available to the public including in ways that members of the public may access the material from a place and at a time individually chosen by them.

“Adapted Material” means material subject to copyright and similar rights that is derived from or based upon the Licensed Material and in which the Licensed Material is translated, altered, arranged, transformed, or otherwise modified in a manner requiring permission under the copyright and similar rights held by the Licensor. For purposes of this Public License, where the Licensed Material is a musical work, performance, or sound recording, Adapted Material is always produced where the Licensed Material is synched in timed relation with a moving image.

“NonCommercial” means not primarily intended for or directed towards commercial advantage or monetary compensation. For purposes of this Public License, the exchange of the Licensed Material for other material subject to copyright and similar rights by digital file-sharing or similar means is NonCommercial provided there is no payment of monetary compensation in connection with the exchange.

“NoDerivatives” means that You may not Share Adapted Material derived from the Licensed Material. This includes, but is not limited to, remixing, transforming, translating, abridging, or otherwise altering the Licensed Material in any manner that creates a new work based upon the original.

“Copyright and Similar Rights” means copyright and/or similar rights closely related to copyright including, without limitation, performance, broadcast, sound recording, and sui generis database rights, without regard to how the rights are labeled or categorized.

“Licensed Rights” means the rights granted to You subject to the terms and conditions of this Public License, which are limited to all Copyright and Similar Rights that apply to Your use of the Licensed Material and that the Licensor has authority to license.

