You may satisfy the conditions in Section 3.1 in any reasonable manner based on the medium, means, and context in which You Share the Licensed Material. It is sufficient to provide a URI or hyperlink to a resource that includes the required information.

3.2 NonCommercial Use Only
You may not exercise any of the rights granted in Section 2.1 in any manner that is primarily intended for or directed toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation. This includes, without limitation:

Selling, licensing for a fee, or otherwise commercially exploiting the Licensed Material;
Using the Licensed Material in connection with paid advertising, sponsored content, or any revenue-generating activity;
Incorporating the Licensed Material into a product or service sold or offered for a fee;
Accepting any form of monetary payment in exchange for access to or copies of the Licensed Material.
Educational, personal, research, or journalistic uses that do not generate direct revenue are generally considered NonCommercial; however, context determines applicability. When in doubt, contact the Licensor for clarification.

3.3 NoDerivatives — No Adapted Material
You may not produce Adapted Material for the purpose of Sharing it publicly. You may not:

Remix, transform, translate, or adapt the Licensed Material in any way;
Build upon the Licensed Material to create a new or derivative work;
Edit, crop, colorize, re-record, reformat (in ways that alter expressive content), or otherwise modify the Licensed Material;
Incorporate any part of the Licensed Material into a larger work or compilation that constitutes an Adapted Material.
Technical format-shifting (e.g., converting a JPEG to PNG for personal use without altering the content) that results in no modification to the expressive content of the Licensed Material may not constitute the creation of Adapted Material. The Licensor makes no warranty as to the permissibility of any specific act not expressly addressed herein.

